Create a B2C Commerce Data Stream

As a Data Cloud admin, you can use the order bundle to create a data stream to flow data from a B2C Commerce instance. A data bundle creates and maps data streams. The order bundle is a type of data bundle. When you deploy the order bundle, custom attributes for your B2C Commerce Goods Product and Master Product entities are available in Data Cloud to map to a data model object (DMO).

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
To create a data stream	Data Cloud Admin or Data Cloud for Marketing Data Aware Specialist Permission Set

To deploy the order bundle, enable Commerce Einstein tracking in your B2C Commerce instance.

In Data Cloud, go to the Data Streams tab and click New.
Select the B2C Commerce data source and click Next.
Select a B2C Commerce instance and click Next.
If you have only one instance connected to Data Cloud, it’s selected by default.
Select the order bundle that includes the order, product, and customer data.
If you have only one instance, its order bundle is selected by default.
Review the fields to include in your data stream, and deselect the fields that you don’t want to include.
To add a formula field, click New Formula Fields.
Add a display name for the Field Label.
If desired, update the Field API name.
Enter the Formula Return Type, which is the field’s data type.
Define a formula using the search function, attributes, and transformation formula options.
Click Save.
When you’re done adding formula fields, review the data stream and click Next.
Click Deploy.
After you deploy the bundle, allow at least 24 hours for the data to ingest.
When you establish a connection between B2C Commerce and Data Cloud, the B2C Commerce Connector ingests 30 days of historical data. For example, if you establish a connection on May 1, the B2C Commerce Connector ingests historical data from April 2 to May 1. From this point forward, the B2C Commerce Connector continues to ingest data.
NOTE The B2C Commerce Connector prevents data ingestion for customers who have opted out of tracking using the B2C Commerce standard do-not-track (DNT) cookie. If a customer has opted in to data tracking and then chooses to opt out of tracking, new data for the customer isn’t ingested into Data Cloud. However, previously ingested data remains within Data Cloud. Customers can use the Data Cloud data deletion feature to remove user data.
